bug.short_desc: Wayland breaks the drawing of non gtk3 applications
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1232322 antialias_off
Description of problem: Latest upgrade of Wayland breaks drawing of non gtk3 applications toolbar icons and other elements.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): gnome-session-wayland-session.x86_64 3.22.2-1.fc25 ibus-wayland.x86_64 1.5.14-3.fc25 libwayland-client.x86_64 1.12.0-1.fc25 libwayland-cursor.x86_64 1.12.0-1.fc25 libwayland-server.x86_64 1.12.0-1.fc25 mesa-libwayland-egl.x86_64 13.0.2-2.fc25 mesa-libwayland-egl-devel.x86_64 13.0.2-2.fc25 wayland-devel.x86_64 1.12.0-1.fc25 wayland-protocols-devel.noarch 1.7-1.fc25 xorg-x11-server-Xwayland.x86_64 1.19.0-1.fc25
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Start Dia. Open/create a new model. Elements are displayed as in "antialias_off.png" screenshot. 2. Enable antialias. Elements are displayed as in "antialias_on.png".
Created attachment 1232324 model to test the bug

I experience the same problem in the GUI using SmartGit (V8.03) and in Shutter (v0.93.1-3.fc25.noarch).
SmartGit is a Java application, while shutter is a Perl Application.
